5000|$|Remunerations or {{earnings}} paid by {{an employer}} to an employee for service rendered are called wages. Article 99 of the Labor Code of the Philippines stipulates that an employer may go over but never below <b>minimum</b> <b>wage.</b> Paying below the <b>minimum</b> <b>wage</b> is illegal. The Regional Tripartite Wages and Productivity Boards {{is the body}} that sets the amount for the <b>minimum</b> <b>wage.</b> <b>As</b> {{in the case of}} the Philippines, the <b>minimum</b> <b>wage</b> of <b>a</b> worker depends on where he works.|$|R
